programme.title: Olympics 2018: Curling (Mixed Doubles): Canada vs. Norway and China vs. Switzerland
programme.sub-title: Curling (Mixed Doubles): Canada vs. Norway and China vs. Switzerland
programme.desc: Canada takes on Norway and China comes face-to-face with Switzerland in the inaugural mixed doubles curling event. China and Switzerland are both favorites, with Switzerland winning the 2017 World Mixed Doubles Championship over Canada. Canada took gold in both the men's and women's events at Sochi in 2014, but have yet to win the top prize in mixed doubles curling at any of the event's world championships (dating back to 2008). (live) (cc)(n)

programme.title: Olympics 2018: Curling (Mixed Doubles): U.S. vs. Canada and China vs. South Korea, Ski Jumping
programme.sub-title: Curling (Mixed Doubles): U.S. vs. Canada and China vs. South Korea, Ski Jumping
programme.desc: Team USA faces off with Canada and hosts South Korea meet rival China in mixed doubles curling. Also: ski jumping. Known as the "flower of ski sports" for its beauty, ski jumping takes place at the Alpensia Ski Jumping Centre. The men, led by Kamil Stoch (Poland), take on the individual normal hill competition. Japan's Noriaki Kasai, still in search of the Olympic gold, is competing in a record-breaking eighth Olympics. (live) (cc)(n)
